This paper deals with a problem of sampling bias in supervised learning, which is a common issue in machine learning. The paper focuses on kernel mean matching (KMM) estimator and its effectiveness under covariate shift. The topic of the paper is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), statistics (cs.ST), and data structures (cs.DS). However, given the focus on supervised learning and the use of kernel methods, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
